The paper deals with stochastic dynamic games with asymmetric information, which are typically studied in the field of game theory (cs.GT). The games involve multiple agents controlling the system dynamics, which suggests a connection to control theory (cs.SY). The agents have different information about the system over time, which involves information theory (cs.IT). The paper also provides a backward induction algorithm to compute the equilibria, which involves optimization and decision-making, suggesting a connection to machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.MA, cs.AI).
